TAIWAN DAYBOOK: Taiwan Aims to Sign China Peace Deal in 10 Years

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-18T00:26:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/taiwan-daybook-taiwan-aims-to-sign-china-peace-deal-in-10-years.html
Taiwan aims to sign a peace
agreement with  China  within 10 years, provided there is domestic
consensus, mutual trust and parliamentary supervision, President
Ma Ying-jeou said in a briefing in Taipei yesterday.  Ma reiterated his mainland policy of “no unification, no
independence and no use of force under the framework of the
 Republic of China  constitution.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  